==English==
===Etymology===
from [[draft]] (itself from to draw) + [[horse]]

===Noun===
'''draft horse''' {{m}}
*a horse used for muscular work, other then carrying a rider and/or load, such as pulling a [[cart]], [[plow]] or [[log]]
*a horse of a race specifically bred for such work, heavy and strong

====Synonym====
*[[draught horse]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[trekpaard]] {{n}}
*German: [[Zugpferd]] {{n}}